---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description={`About Numeric Oasis. A software house and consulting company with 15 years across Atlassian, SaaS, and IT services.`}
>
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-50 to-white py-20 sm:py-28">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <p class="eyebrow">About us</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 max-w-4xl font-display text-4xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl">
        A small studio with a long view.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
        We are a software house and consulting company based in {SITE.location}. Fifteen years of designing, building, advising on, and supporting software. Heavy on Atlassian and SaaS, with deep roots in business and IT service consulting.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 sm:py-24">
    <div class="container-prose">
      <div class="prose-custom">
        <h2>What we do</h2>
        <p>
          Four practices, one team. We <strong>build</strong> custom SaaS, web and mobile apps, and Atlassian Forge apps for the Marketplace. We <strong>advise</strong> on Atlassian platform health, business and IT processes, ITIL, and governance. We <strong>support</strong> the teams using what we ship, with SLA backed managed services. The same people you talk to about strategy are the ones writing the code and answering the support tickets.
        </p>

        <h2>15 years, four practices</h2>
        <p>
          Numeric Oasis brings fifteen years of consulting, software development, customer support, business analysis, and process implementation. That history is why we resist drawing a hard line between "software" and "operations". Customers rarely have just a software problem or just a process problem. They have a both kind of problem, and the answer is usually both.
        </p>

        <h2>How we work</h2>
        <p>
          Small teams. Direct contact with the people doing the building. Short feedback loops, real release cadence, and honest assessments of what is worth shipping vs. what is not. We pick scope carefully and say no when we should.
        </p>

        <h2>Where Atlassian fits</h2>
        <p>
          Atlassian is one of our deepest specialties, not our entire identity. We are an Atlassian Marketplace partner with apps already in production on Jira, Confluence, and Jira Service Management. We also do the platform consulting around them: migrations, audits, performance work, and Marketplace strategy. When a customer's problem is best solved with Atlassian, we use it. When it is not, we say so.
        </p>

        <h2>Why "Numeric Oasis"</h2>
        <p>
          Because the work we love most lives at the intersection of clean numbers and breathing room. Data you can trust, and software that gives you space to think.
        </p>

        <h2>Where we are</h2>
        <p>
          Headquartered in {SITE.location}. We work across Brazilian, European, and US East time zones. Most of our calls are async. Most of our async is in writing.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
